The paper discusses the use of neural networks for predicting molecular properties and bioactivities, which falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on drug discovery, which involves chemical structures and their properties, making it relevant to the sub-category of chemical informatics (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the identification of relevant components of a compound, which can be seen as a data mining task (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of extracted pharmacophores, which is a topic in computational chemistry (cs.CHEM).
